 "text", "text": ", and there is no instance, in the language, of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tafaEolana", "text_ar": "تَفَعْلَنَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Har p. 102;) it signifies The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "headman,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "chief, of a village"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "town:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Es-Sem'ánee, Msb, TA: [agreeably with the Pers. original:]) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "proprietor thereof, in Khurásán and El-' Irák:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Es-Sem'ánee, TA:) or, as used by the Arabs,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a great man of the unbelievers of the ' Ajam"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Persians"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: but they disdained this appellation: (Mgh:) Lth says that it is a nickname, or name of reproach: (TA:) it became predominantly applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such of them as was of the people of the districts of cultivated land and of villages or towns:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and then to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "anyone possessing much land or other immoveable property:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh:) [it signifies generally"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a dweller,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one having a fixed abode, in a district of cultivated land,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in a village or town of such a district; a rustic; a husbandman:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] or it signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a chief, headman,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "person in authority, over the husbandmen,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "peasants, of the 'Ajam"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Persians"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "headman of a province:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a possessor of land or other immoveable property:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a merchant:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, K:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one who manages affairs firmly,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "strongly, with sharpness:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) the fem. is with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (JK, Mgh, K:) and the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dahaAqiynu", "text_ar": "دَهَاقِينُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dahaAqinapN", "text_ar": "دَهَاقِنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) [See a verse cited voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ja*aA", "text_ar": "جَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "j*w", "text_ar": "جذو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". The same verse, but with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaroyatiY", "text_ar": "قَرْيَتِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(my village or town) in the place of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaroyapK", "text_ar": "قَرْيَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", is also cited in the TA in the present art.]"}], "source_refs": ["JK", "Msb", "K", "TA", "S", "Kh", "Sb", "Mgh"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}